\n<\N[5]>(I had a feeling when that siren went
off... Shit... This is bad, how do we
get through this?)

Immediately after passing through the mountain
road, we were forced to stop by two cars
that were waiting and provoking us.
\n<\N[5]>Sawa, how are the police officers?
\n<Sawa>Yes, I told them to come right away... Ah...

\n<Kino>Tch... It seems like those guys aren't just
waiting leisurely.

Kino, who was made to get in the car for
their safety, leaned out of the back
seat and pointed forward.

Men are coming out one after another from
the cars parked ahead.

\n<Kino>What should we do? If we stay holed up like
this, we'll definitely get caught. It
seems like those guys are skilled in
this kind of 'rough business'.

Kino must have felt that way after seeing
how skillfully those guys forced us to
stop... On that point, I agree too.

\n<\N[5]>(If that's the case... Should we just get
out of the car and run away? If I stay
behind, I can hold some of them back...)

\n<Kino>...If we're going to do it, I'll go along.
It's my mistake that it came to this...

It seems like Kino was thinking the same
thing.
\n<Sawa>N-No... That's, that's absolutely not allowed!
\n<\N[5]>...Minato?

Minato was staring at me... with a troubled
expression and a smile.
\n<Minato>...I guess there's no other choice.
Minato unlocks the door on the passenger side.
\n<\N[5]>H-Hey! What are you doing----...

\n<Minato>Is Udo targeting me? If that's the case...
I'll go out and try to settle things
somehow...

\n<\N[5]>Don't say stupid things! Do you think we
would be happy about that?!

\n<Minato>...You'll probably get angry. But it's better
than getting our important comrades
involved.
\n<\N[5]>Ah, I see... You're that kind of person.
I grip the steering wheel again.

\n<\N[5]>Minato... If you decide to leave, I won't
hesitate to run over those guys with
this car.
\n<Minato>Ngh...

\n<\N[5]>It's better to sacrifice yourself. I will
get caught as a criminal... but you all
will definitely be saved.

\n<Kino>Hehe, well that's fine♪ I'll go along with
it♪

\n<Sawa>Wait... Let's calm down for a moment... Hey,
can you say something too, Momo?

Momo, who had been silently looking outside
the car, speaks up.
\n<Momo>...Hey, hey, don't you hear something?
\n<Sawa>Huh...? What do you mean you hear something...
\n<Minato>...Ah... It's true... This is...
\n<Kino>----...! Can you please turn off the engine!
\n<\N[5]>W-What the hell...

I was hesitant to turn off the engine,
but I reluctantly did as they said...
And then, I could clearly hear it too.

\n<Sawa>W-What... Could it be that we were called by our
comrades...
\n<Kino>It's the opposite... Geez, making us wait...
\n<Men>Huh? What the hell...?
\n<Men>H-Hey... Won't you come over here?
\n<Men>No way... It's just a coincidence, right?
\n<Men>No... We're almost there...

The men turned around... and we also caught
sight of it in our field of vision. We
turned the corner ahead and saw a group
of motorcycles rushing towards us like a
muddy stream...

\n<Men>Oh, could it be that those guys are the
same as us...?

\n<Men>Ah, I see... Tch, are they trying to steal
our credit?

A group of men on motorcycles gathered on
the other side, and among them, several
dozen men who were leading the way got
off their bikes and slowly walked
towards us.

......I understood at a glance. Those men are
completely different from the thugs who
were cornering us.

Each person exuded a dangerous aura, as if
they were accustomed to violence in
their daily lives.
\n<Men>H-Hey... Maybe they're not the ones after all?

\n<Men>Ah... Ahh! I... I have a promise with a girl!
So, I'm fine... You guys can take the
credit!
\n<Men>Ah! H-Hey...

The men who couldn't hide their agitation,
one by one... slipped through the side
of the tough- looking men and fled.
\n<\N[5]>C-Could it be... are they old acquaintances?

However, Kino showed a puzzled expression and
shook their head.

\n<Kino>What are they... I'll go check them out for
a moment.

Kino, who said that, stepped out of the car
without hesitation and approached the
men. I hurriedly followed after her.

\n<Kino>Who the hell are you guys... where are you
from?

Unfortunately, I hide in Kino's shadow and observe the
situation.

With that voice, the group in front of me
split in half, and from the center, one
woman approached.

\n<？？？>Geez... If you're so nervous that you can't
speak in front of the real thing, then
you shouldn't be leading the way.
\n<Stern Man>S-Sorry...
\n<Kino>Y-You...

\n<\N[5]>(W-What?! Are they enemies? Are they enemies?!
I-I'll do it too if I have to!)

While hiding in Kino's shadow, I warm up with
some sharp shadow boxing in my mind.

\n<？？？>Long time no see. You haven't changed a bit,
reckless Kino.

\n<Kino>You've changed, Neon. You've completely taken
on the face of a mother.

\n<\N[5]>(Are they an ally? They're an ally, right?
Alright...)
I stand beside Kino.

\n<Kino>Ah, don't worry, \N[5]-san... This is an
old acquaintance, Neon. And this is our
manager, \N[5]-san.

\n<Enka>Nice to meet you, I'm Enka. Kino always
takes care of me.
\n<\N[5]>U-Um, this is \N[5]. Today is a good day...

\n<\N[5]>(An arranged marriage?! N-No, but more
importantly... They seem like a decent
person. I apologize for being on guard
just because they're an acquaintance of
Kino...)

\n<Kino>So... who are those guys? I don't recognize
any of their faces...

\n<Enka>Ah... Those are my husband's junior
colleagues.

\n<Stern Man>Hey, hey, Neon-san! That's a bit much!
Please introduce them properly!

\n<Enka>You're so noisy... Well, if I start talking,
it'll get long...

\n<Enka>After I received a message from Kino, I tried
to contact my former colleagues, but it
was late at night... and I couldn't
reach them.

\n<Enka>So when I told my husband about it, he
gathered people for me...

\n<Kino>Ah, my husband used to be a delinquent
too... But I can't believe we gathered
such a group...

Certainly... When I glanced at the group of people
straddling motorcycles, there were
roughly 50 or 60 of them.

\n<Enka>Well, rather than my husband's influence...
it might be your influence. Somehow, the
word got out that I might be able to
meet AlterGuns...
\n<Kino>What... are you here for Neon?
\n<Stern Man A>I'm a Kino fan! Only Kino can win!

\n<Stern Man B>Ah! You...! I've been a fan since the days
of 'Fireball Neon'!
\n<Kino>Huh!?
\n<\N[5]>Fireball...? What's that?
\n<Kino>N-Nothing! It's fine here, so go back to the car.
\n<Momo>Tell me more.
\n<Kino>What the hell, they're all gathering up!!

\n<Enka>That... I wonder if it was during the conflict
between us, the 'Extreme Evil
Butterfly,' and Jirai Gen, who were
sworn enemies?

\n<Enka>Someone described Kino, dressed in crimson
special attire, running straight towards
the enemy, as a 'fireball' for the first
time.

\n<Stern Man C>So, the legend of the 'Fireball' started
from that day, huh...
\n<Kino>Ugh...ah...ahh...ahhh...Ahhh!!

\n<Minato>Calm down, Kino! You look cool, Fireball
Kino! In English, it would be
'Fireball'... Hahaha!

Following Minato's self-destructive follow-up,
laughter breaks out here and there.
\n<Kino>Y-You guys, geez!!

\n<Enka>Then let's join up with the main unit. We
just need to escort them outside of
town, right?

\n<Kino>Ah...hmm? The main unit? Are there others besides
us?

\n<Enka>Hey, you... Don't underestimate our
influence.

\n<Enka>Despite it being late at night, everyone
gathered... a total of 300 people! It
was quite a challenge to organize them
all.

\n<Kino>So, 300... I see, that's why we were
late...

I felt amazed... not by the number 300,
but by the fact that I have a friend
like Enka. She acted purely for Kino's
sake and rushed to our aid. I wonder...
do I have even one friend like that...

\n<Kino>I've ended up with a huge debt... Thanks,
Enka.

\n<Enka>Don't be conceited, who do you think came
rushing here for your sake! Of course, I
came to see Minato- sama!
\n<Kino>Uwaaahhhhh!!!

Kino covers their face with both hands and
crouches down in that spot.

\n<Enka>Minato-sama! Please give me your autograph! Oh, it
would be great if you could write it as
'Enka'!
\n<Minato>Ah, ah... Is it okay...?

\n<Enka>There's no problem. That child... enjoys being
bullied, so...
\n<Kino>Th-th-there's no way that's true!
\n<\N[5]>Shall we go back to the car?

\n<Sawa>Hehe, that's right. Let's go back... Huh? I
can't find Momo...
\n<\N[5]>Huh!? They were there just a moment ago...

\n<\N[5]>(Ah, there you are! What are you doing in
such a distant place...)
\n<Stern Big Man>「.........」
\n<Stern Big Man>U-um...
\n<Momo>You're big~ How old are you?
\n<Stern Big Man>Eh... I-I'm 17!

\n<Momo>Ahaha, it's not about age~ It's about height,
silly~

Momo vigorously slaps the back of the stern
big man.

\n<\N[5]>(Hey... You shouldn't casually touch someone of
that age like that...)
\n<Stern Big Man>Wha-what!? I-I'm 195!
\n<\N[5]>(Ah... Poor thing... I was too late...)

\n<Momo>Whoa~ It's almost 2 meters! Alright then,
here you go!

Momo turned her back to the stern big man
and stretched out both arms to the
sides.
\n<Stern Big Man>Eh... W-what is it?

\n<\N[5]>(Well, no wonder he's confused... What is that
person doing...)
\n<Momo>High, high~ Give it a try~
\n<Stern Big Man>Huh... Huh? Huh!?
\n<Momo>Hey~ Come on, hurry up and do it \I[12]!
\n<\N[5]>(......S-Something feels lewd)
\n<Stern Big Man>Uh... E-excuse me...

The stern big man wiped his palms
vigorously with his own clothes, and
then swiftly lifted up the offering he
had brought to Momo's side.

\n<Momo>Whoa~ Amazing! So this is the view from 2
meters!
\n<Stern Big Man>Haha, is that so... huh?

The stern big man turned around and saw the
men who had escaped earlier in the
square facing the road.
\n<The returning men>Ah! It's them!

\n<Muscular Man>Oh... You're not an amateur, huh? Looks like
this is gonna be fun!

Leading the way was a muscular man, followed by
the men who had escaped earlier. Behind
them, several dozen men were also
following.
\n<Stern Big Man>...Momo-san, please go. We will take care of this.

The stern big man gently set Momo down and
turned his face towards me.

\n<Stern Big Man>Hey! You're the manager, right? It's
dangerous here, so take Momo with you!
\n<\N[5]>Momo! Come here, get in the car!
\n<Momo>Eh... U-um... but...

\n<Stern Big Man>No problem, I got this. Go on... I'll be
cheering for you the whole time!

\n<Momo>Thank you... Watch me, okay! I'll do my best,
Momo will give it her all~!

Momo and I got into the car. Minato had
moved to the back seat and was being
embraced by Sawa.
\n<\N[5]>...Minato, are you okay?
\n<Minato>Haha... I can't seem to stop shaking...

\n<\N[5]>(It's not surprising... If a group of men
like that were coming to capture me,
even as a male, I would be trembling in
fear...)
\n<Enka>We'll lead the way! Don't fall behind, Kino!

\n<Kino>Huh, who are you talking to? Did you give
birth to a brat and lose your mind?

\n<Enka>Huh? Geez... You still have a foul mouth,
huh?

Perhaps it is their usual interaction, but
their normalcy in this situation is
quite reassuring. That's why even
someone like me, a commoner, can somehow
maintain composure.

\n<\N[5]>(......Don't worry, we will return safely.
Because...)

Sawa reached out her hand to me, who was
alone, and supported me all along. Momo
gave us weapons to fight against the
great evil, even though we were
defenseless. And Kino... Kino overcame
fear and despair with absolute strength.

\n<\N[5]>(It's a lie that we won't be saved after
coming this far. Such an ending should
only exist in stories.)
\n<\N[5]>Alright... Let's go!

If even one person was missing... it
wouldn't have turned out like this. And
this is not a miracle... it is the
result of the actions we, me and them,
have woven together.

We... we have finally arrived at the place we
almost lost----...

\n<Police Officer A>W-Wait... I didn't hear anything like that...
H-Hey! What do we do?!

\n<Officer B>What are we supposed to do... This is
hopeless...

\n<Police Officer A>Then... I'll, I'll report it for now! I'll
inform Udo-san right away--...

\n<Officer B>That... it hasn't been connecting at all since
earlier... Damn it! What the hell is
going on...

\n<Police Officer A>Haha... This isn't good... It seems like it
would be best to pack up our things
tonight...

And... the police officers stood dumbfounded,
silently watching the muddy stream
flowing down the main street...

It was an impressive sight. There were so
many motorcycles surrounding the car we
were in that we couldn't even count
them.

\n<\N[5]>Haha... I feel like I've become an important
person who is being protected by a
motorcade...

\n<Minato>Is that so? With all this commotion, it
feels less like protection and more like
a little parade, doesn't it?

\n<Momo>That's right! Somehow, I'm getting all...
excited~!

\n<Sawa>Just because of that, don't stick your head
out of the window! I'm not a child, you
know!

......I understand the feeling. I, who am
saying this, am also feeling excited.
\n<Minato>It's over... Really...

Her trembling had stopped. Seeing that,
there was a sense of relief... but at
the same time, a slight feeling of
regret remained.

I couldn't even comfort her properly when
she was scared. We were able to come
this far mostly thanks to Sawa and the
other two.
\n<\N[5]>(I'm... really useless, aren't I...)

Soon, we will pass through the main street.
Once I safely escort her... I will think
about what to do with my life.

I... no, I exposed them to danger. I have to
take responsibility for that.

I should... probably leave from in front
of them. I was originally lacking in
strength... I had a faint feeling about
that. If it wasn't me... by now, they
would have been shining even more----...

\n<Enka>We've come this far, so we should be fine.
It's about time for us to take our
leave.

After each of us expressed our gratitude to
Enka-san... Kino took a step forward.

\n<Kino>It was good to be able to run with you
again after a long time. And... I really
appreciate your help.

\n<Enka>Why don't you show up in your hometown once
in a while? Everyone is eagerly
anticipating and cheering for your
success, you know.
\n<Kino>Yeah... Ah, let's do that.

Enka-san mounted the bike with a gallant
gesture, waved at us once, and then
revved the engine, speeding away with a
loud roar. The men followed suit,
forming a turbulent stream once again.
\n<Momo>Ah... Manen-chan! Look over there!

Momo looked at where she was pointing, and
saw that intimidating big man and his
companions running away proudly, raising
their arms.
\n<\N[5]>...They were a pleasant bunch.
\n<Kino>Ah, yeah...

They showed a rare lonely expression.
However... it was just for a moment, and
they quickly returned to their usual
self and turned towards me.

\n<Kino>I want to talk with the four of us for a
moment. Sorry, but \N[5]-san, could you
step aside for a bit...
\n<\N[5]>Huh... Ah, yeah... Then I'll wait in the car.

......I somehow sensed it. They are probably
confessing their sins to Minato.

\n<\N[5]>It'll be alright... This isn't the end,
right?

However... it is Minato who will decide that. No
matter what answer she gives, we have no
right to blame her.

Even though I know that, I can't help but be
curious, so I peek at their behavior
outside the window.

Minato... was alone, looking down. It was too
dark to confirm their expression, but it
seemed like they were crying.

It might have been a cruel truth for her,
who was exhausted both mentally and
physically. Should I have measured the
timing to confess with more
consideration for her?

No... It's not for me to say anything. Even
those three understand that. It's a
decision to confess now.

I might have been naive. Simply sending
them back to their everyday lives won't
solve anything. They are individuals
with their own thoughts, and they will
continue to live on in the future...

I can only wait helplessly... and it's
pathetic. That's why I pray. Even if we
can no longer continue our activities
together as we have been, please, I hope
that the relationship between the four
of them will not be broken.
I could only wish for it like a child...

They walked over to me, so I stepped out of
the car.

\n<Minato>\N[5]-san... I won't stop. I can't give up on
something like this...

Minato said only that and then... got on the
bike alone.

\n<Kino>...Sorry, but from here on, I'll be going my own
way.
\n<Momo>Mane-chan, go home with Minato, okay?
\n<\N[5]>Huh... What do you mean by that?

...I couldn't find the words. I couldn't ask
any further. It felt unfair to hear the
details without Minato, who was waiting
alone in a distant place...
\n<Sawa>I'm counting on you, Minato...
The three of them got into the car.

\n<Kino>There was a helmet in the trunk, right? Take
it with you.

\n<Sawa>Well then, we'll go ahead... since we'll be
riding together, be careful while
driving, okay?

\n<Minato>Ah, I understand. Sawa and the others
too...
\n<Momo>Well then, see you~...

And so... leaving me and Neon behind, Sawa
and the others also left.

\n<\N[5]>...Should we change the time? I'll go buy
something.
\n<Minato>Ah, ah... Yeah, I understand. I'll do it.

\n<Minato>...I'm sorry for not saying anything, but what
is this...

\n<\N[5]>Refreshing and exhilarating! How about some
carbonated cocoa?

\n<Minato>So don't try to test it on me! Exchange it
with that person!

\n<\N[5]>It's not a big deal... but this one is
shisomeru tea, you know?

\n<Minato>More shisomeru tea! What is it? Do you like
it? Are you secretly addicted to it?!

\n<\N[5]>No, I was thinking of cutting off Minato's
retreat...
\n<Minato>If we both die... I'll lose my friends...

\n<\N[5]>Ah, I only do it with Minato, so it's not a
problem.
\n<Minato>~~~~~~~
\n<Minato>Mmm, mmm, mmm, mmm, mmm...

Neon, who became desperate, quickly gulped
down the mysterious... I mean, highly
anticipated new product.
\n<Minato>Puhh... Huh? This is actually pretty good...
\n<\N[5]>You're kidding... That's so stupid...

\n<Minato>Well then, it's \N[5]'s turn. Come on, take
a sip♪

\n<Minato>Even if you make such a serious face, I
won't forgive you. Come on, hurry up and
take a sip.

......The unpleasant sweetness lingering in my
mouth is quite nauseating. However, I
want to praise myself for managing to
drink it all without leaving any behind.
And then, I turn towards Minato and
throw the empty bottle into the trash
can.
\n<\N[5]>Well then, Neon, shall we go soon?
\n<Minato>Huh?!

Minato, who was playing with her smartphone a
little away from me, let out a high-
pitched voice.
\n<Minato>Ahem... Ah, wait a moment.

I thought it was suspicious... but I
decided to stop pursuing it because it
could lead to sexual harassment... What
a troublesome world we live in.
\n<Minato>...----Hyauu!? D-Don't touch my side!

\n<Minato>I'll rely on the grab bar or your
shoulder... (※A handlebar attached along
the back seat.)

Riding on the tandem seat was my first
experience, so I was nervous. However...
there was another reason for my
nervousness.

\n<\N[5]>Just to make sure... Are you okay? Have you
ever ridden tandem before?
\n<Minato>What? Are you doubting my driving skills?

\n<\N[5]>Yeah, well... I've had some pretty
spectacular falls in the past...

\n<Minato>Ah, it's different from back then! Leave it
to me!

She... has a previous record of bleeding from
her head and coming to work. I'm sorry,
but I can't trust Neon. And besides...
\n<Minato>Alright! Let's go! Hold on tight!

\n<\N[5]>(This is definitely influenced by those guys
earlier... That excited attitude just
seems fake to me now...)

\n<\N[5]>Father, Mother... Please forgive me for leaving
you behind...
\n<Minato>Hehe... Stop it, don't make me laugh.
A
A
